Lovie Smith  was fired as coach of
the Chicago Bears six seasons after leading them to a berth in
the Super Bowl.  The Beras missed the playoffs yesterday when the Minnesota
Vikings beat the Green Bay Packers. Chicago finished the season
10-6.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
